Setting Up Your New iPhone?
💽 **Data Transfer from Android to iPhone**:
 Learn how to transfer data from an Android to an iPhone using Apple’s Move to iOS app:

 - Set up your new iOS device until you reach the “Apps & Data” screen. 📲
 - Tap “Move Data from Android.” 📱
 - On your Android device, download and install the “Move to iOS” app from the Google Play Store. 🛍️
 - Open the “Move to iOS” app on your Android device and tap “Continue.” ▶️
 - On your iOS device, tap “Continue” when prompted on the “Move from Android” screen. 🔄
 - Agree to the terms and conditions on your Android device. ✅
 - Enter the code displayed on your iOS device into the “Move to iOS” app on your Android device. 🔢
 - Connect your Android device to the temporary Wi-Fi network created by your iOS device. 📶
 - Select the content you want to transfer from your Android to your iOS device. 📁
 - Tap “Next” and wait for the transfer to complete. ⌛

M – your iPhone is new
F – your iPhone is refurbished (refurbished by Apple or a carrier)
N – your iPhone is an Apple replacement phone
P – your iPhone was personalized with engraving

•🚫 Gambling and betting are illegal in India, yet numerous apps like 1X**, Lot365, Fairp** thrive. How is this possible?

•📊 These brands are intentionally promoted in the market, often with the help of celebrities and influencers.

•🌐 Some of these endorsements are misleading. For example, Yuvraj Singh promotes a company blacklisted by the Britain Gambling Commission (source 1).

•📰 Surrogate advertising is used by many apps, falsely claiming to be news websites rather than gambling platforms, which violates the Consumer Protection Act (source 1.1).

•📵 Despite government bans, these apps frequently appear on newspaper front pages and the profiles of prominent influencers and celebrities.

•🤔 Interestingly, Dream11 and MPL are legal due to the skill element involved. However, games of pure chance remain illegal.

•🛡 To maintain their legality, some companies exploit a loophole in the 1867 Public Gambling Act, which only prohibits physical gambling, not online gambling (source 3)
•Source 1: 
https://www.deccanherald.com/sports/cricket/blacklisted-betting-site-makes-backdoor-entry-in-india-with-asia-cup-1144359.html

https://www.clearias.com/surrogate-advertisement/#central-consumer-protection-authority-guidelines

Which Processor You Should Prefer?
[ Intel vs AMD ]
Intel called it’s processor ‘core’ & AMD called it’s processor ‘Ryzen’.
Higher number of processors will always have better performance. Like Ryzen 7 is better from Ryzen 5 and Intel i7 is better from Intel i5.
Here are use cases of processors serieses (U-P-H) :-
1. Basic Programming, Word, Excel and Web Browsing:- Intel U and AMD U series.
2. Graphic Designing and sometimes gaming at 1080p:- Intel P series.
3. Video Editing in 4k and high quality gaming:- AMD H series.
4. Pro Gamers and Pro Editors:- Intel HK series, AMD HX series and AMD HS series.
Note: You have to see the last letter of processors, like i5 1240P, so you have to put attention on P for determining the series of Intel and AMD
.

.
Choose Right Graphics Card : 
1. Compatibility: Ensure the graphics card fits your laptop/PC’s slot (e.g., PCIe) and power supply.
2. Performance: Choose a recent version (e.g., NVIDIA GTX 30 series or AMD RX 6000 series) for better gaming and productivity.
3. Wattage: Opt for a card with adequate wattage (e.g., 100-300W) to handle your tasks without overloading your PSU.
4. VRAM: More VRAM (e.g., 8GB or 16GB) supports higher resolution gaming and multitasking.
5. Budget: Balance performance and cost to get the best graphics card for your needs
.

🔢 Excel Tricks :

1️⃣ Freeze the First Row: To keep the top row fixed even when scrolling, move your cursor below the header and press Alt + W F F. Your header will stay in place.

2️⃣ Fit Large Data on One Page: When your data won't fit on a single page, head to Page Layout, set the width to 'One Page,' and print. Your data will automatically adjust to one page.

3️⃣ Delete Blank Cells Efficiently: Instead of deleting blank cells one by one, select all your data, press F5, choose 'Special,' select 'Blanks,' click 'OK.' Now, press Ctrl - and shift up. Voilà, all blanks are gone! 🚀

• Fact #1: The world’s most valuable company, Apple 🍎, makes a staggering $1,820 (over Rs 1.48 lakh) every second, making the iPhone maker the world's most profitable company, generating about $157 million (more than Rs 1,282 crore) a day.
-------------------------------------------------
• Fact #2: The world's first mouse 🖱️, invented by Douglas Engelbart in 1964, was made of wood. It consisted of a simple wooden box with two wheels and a button. The wheels tracked the mouse's movement on a surface, while the button was used for selecting items on the screen. It was not used diagonally because the wheels that tracked the mouse's movement could only move in two directions.
-------------------------------------------------
• Fact #3: The IBM 350, released in 1956, was the world's first hard disk 💽. It was massive, weighing over a ton and the size of two refrigerators. Despite its size, it could store 3.75 MB of data, paving the way for modern hard drives.
-------------------------------------------------
• Fact #4: Placing your phone in Airplane mode 🛩️ while charging can significantly speed up the charging process. This mode turns off your phone's transmitter, including cellular, Bluetooth, radio, and WiFi services, which consume power even when not in use.
-------------------------------------------------

Learn how to Check Battery Health in Windows Laptop:

• STEP 1️⃣: Search and run Command Prompt as administrator.

• STEP 2️⃣: Enter “powercfg /batteryreport” in the command prompt and Press Enter.
Here you will get a Path , Copy that path.

• STEP 3️⃣: Paste that Path in File Explorer’s Top Address Bar.

• STEP 4️⃣: You Will be Redirected to battery report HTML file to view battery details.

Calculate Battery Health Percentage: Full Charge Capacity ÷ Designed Capacity x 100. (e.g., 81.8%)

Remove Bloatwares Apps From Your Phones :-
• STEP 1️⃣: Firstly, Download Platform Tools from by searching “Platform Tools” on Google and Click on this link :”developer.android.com” & Download according to your PC (Mac , Linux or Windows) .
• STEP 2️⃣: Extract the zip file and Paste it into C drive.
• STEP 3️⃣: Download “Universal Debloater Tool” from GitHub link , under “Assets” download these two files “uad_gui_windows-opengl.exe” & “uad_gui_windows.exe” and Paste them into “Platform Tools” Folder.
• STEP 4️⃣: Make your You have enabled USB Debugging from Developer Options , if you don’t know how to enable it , Google it .
• STEP 5️⃣: Connect your Phone with USB.
• STEP 6️⃣: Run any one of these two files “uad_gui_windows-opengl.exe” OR “uad_gui_windows.exe”.
• STEP 7️⃣: Select the packages (bloatware apps) you want to remove from the provided list, and then click on the “Uninstall selection” option located at the bottom right of the tool’s interface.
• STEP 8️⃣: If you ever wish to restore certain packages, you can do so by selecting “Uninstalled” or “Disabled” from the drop-down menu and clicking on “Restore selection.”
• STEP 9️⃣: In case an app doesn’t appear in the debloater list, you can address this by installing “Package Name Viewer 2.0” from the Play Store. This will help you find the app’s package name and enable you to uninstall the corresponding bloatware.

3 iPhone 📱 Hacks:
• HACK 1️⃣ : Never miss important Calls 📞 while keeping notifications silent:
- Enable “Emergency Bypass” for specific contacts under “Ringtone” settings.
- Your mom and dad’s calls won’t be blocked, even in “Do Not Disturb” mode.

• HACK 2️⃣: - Locking apps on your iPhone is now easy.
- Make sure your iPhone is running the latest software version.
- Open the “Shortcuts” app and tap on “Create Personal Automation.”
- Select the app on which you want to enable the lock, for example, Instagram.
- Tap “Next” and search for “Lock Screen” > Tap “Next” > Turn off “Ask Before Running” > Tap “Done.”
- Now, only your face ID or PIN will unlock Instagram.

• HACK 3️⃣: Take control 🎛️of your data privacy:
- Prevent apps from tracking and selling your information.
- In “Settings,” search for “Tracking.”
- Disable tracking for the apps you choose.
- Keep your data in your hands.

Create Custom Ringtones with GarageBand! 🎵🔔
Follow these Steps using GarageBand App :
• STEP 1️⃣: Download the desired ringtone from Safari browser.
• STEP 2️⃣: Launch GarageBand on your iPhone.
• STEP 3️⃣: Tap the plus (+) icon in the top right corner.
• STEP 4️⃣: Select Audio Recorder in the Tracks tab.
• STEP 5️⃣: Click on the third icon in the top left corner.
• STEP 6️⃣: Tap the Loop icon in the top right corner.
• STEP 7️⃣: Choose the Files tab.
• STEP 8️⃣: Select ‘Browse items’ from the Files app.
• STEP 9️⃣: Tap the downloaded audio track you want to set as your ringtone.
• STEP 🔟: The track will be imported to the Files section of Loop.
• STEP 1️⃣1️⃣: Drag the imported file to the left side of the screen.
• STEP 1️⃣2️⃣: Tap the button in the top left corner.
• STEP 1️⃣3️⃣: Select ‘My Songs’.
• STEP 1️⃣4️⃣: Optionally, rename the project.
• STEP 1️⃣5️⃣: Click and hold on the project, then choose ‘Share’.
• STEP 1️⃣6️⃣: Select ‘Ringtone’ in the middle of the screen.
• STEP 1️⃣7️⃣: Tap ‘Export’ in the top right corner.
• STEP 1️⃣8️⃣: Find your custom ringtone in the Sounds & Haptics section of the Settings app, and set it as your iPhone’s ringtone. 🎶📲

Now you can personalize your iPhone with your favorite tunes! Enjoy the sound of uniqueness & Follow @tech_iela for such amazing content.😉💫

Stop third-party apps from collecting data on Android
Limit location sharing:
Go to Settings > Location
Choose specific apps to modify their location permissions
Turn off diagnostic data sharing and marketing information:
Go to Settings > Privacy
Toggle off Send diagnostic data & Receive marketing information
Turn off ads personalization:
Go to Settings > Google
Tap Ads. Toggle on Opt out of ads personalization
Depending on your Android model, you may need to go to Settings > Privacy to access this option
Delete or reset your Advertising ID.
Remove permissions from apps:
Go to Settings > Privacy > Permission manager
Choose and tap a permission to modify settings
Choose the app and tap Don’t Allow, Ask every time or Allow only while using the app

Step 3. Enter your Aadhaar number, captcha code and click on “Send OTP”
Step 4. Enter the OTP.
Step 5. Under Services, click on “Update Aadhaar Online” to update your name, gender, date of birth, address and language written on your Aadhaar card
Step 6. On the next page, click on “Proceed to Update Aadhaar”
Step 7. Choose the Aadhaar details that you want to update and click on “Proceed to Update Aadhaar”. 
Step 8. Enter the details that you want to update/change and upload scanned copies of the supporting documents
Step 9.  Pay the online update fee of Rs. 50 
The update process usually takes up to 90 days to complete. Once updated, you can download the updated version and get your Aadhar card print out.
How to Link Your PAN with Adhaar:
Step 1. Visit https://eportal.incometax.gov.in/iec/foservices/#/pre-login/bl-link-aadhaar
Step 2: Enter your PAN and Aadhaar number and click on “Validate”.

Step 3: Fill in the necessary details and click on the “Link Aadhaar” button.
Step 4: Enter the 6-digit OTP that you receive on the mobile number mentioned in the previous step.

This is How you rent a Car in Dubai ! 🚘 
To Apply for IDP International Driving Permit, Go to sarathi.parivahan.gov.in/
And upload the required documents.
Then You need to go to Your RTO for a Photograph and Verification. This whole process takes maximum 1 Week.

Now when you reach Dubai, You’ll find many car rentals. Just call them to know the exact rates.
The Prices of the Cars can Change with time as they charge more during the peak season. But you can always bargain to get a better price.
You do get a basic Insurance Cover.
But if you buy the Full insurance, it is mostly 30% of the Car Rent Value.
If there is an extra driver, You’ll have to pay 300AED per person.
5% VAT on Car Rent Amount is Compulsory.
Now you will have to pay a security deposit of AED2000-AED5000 depending on the car value from your Credit Card.
This amount will be refunded back to Your account if you don’t get any tickets.
To check if you have received a challan/ticket just download the Dubai police app and you’ll get the whole Information of tickets for Your car.

Do Remember there’s a speed limit within the city. So just take your car to Half Desert Road where there’s no Speed Limit.
That’s it. Enjoy Your Ride !

Is Google really spying on me? 🕵🏻
👉🏻 The simple answer is yes: Google collects data about how you use its devices, apps, and services.
It uses targeted advertising to serve you Google ads that align with your personal tastes.

The kind of data Google collects includes:
•The language(s) you speak.
•The things you buy and your spending budget.
•The places you look up in Google Maps and where you’ve been.
•Your favorite shops, especially if you link your rewards cards to •Google Pay.
•Everything that goes on in your inbox — all your emails, attachments, and even the stuff you mark as spam or delete.
•Everything you save in your Google Drive — work documents, purchase receipts, photos, videos, and so on.
•Your YouTube viewing habits, including everything you’ve ever watched, any comments you’ve ever left, and anything you’ve ever searched for.
•What your upcoming schedule looks like (and everything you’ve done that was in your Google Calendar).
•The apps you open (if you’re using Android) and when you opened them.  
•The questions you ask your Google Assistant.
•All the articles you read on Google News.
👉🏻By using the apps we’ve discussed in the video, you can avoid your data to be collected by anyone. Thus improve your privacy on internet.

•Proton Mail is an end-to-end encrypted email service that is Totally Secure.
•Maples Mapmyindia can be a good replacement for Google Maps if you’re afraid that your location can be used as data by google.
•DuckDuckGo is another Browser that is best replacement for Google Chrome. It is the most secure browser if you want to be secure on internet.

2. Teespring
Teespring is a POD (Print-On-Demand) platform where you can design t-shirts and other products Such as : Socks, Mugs, and Hoodies etc. 
All products are made on-demand, so there are no upfront costs or risks involved. Teesprings makes the product, ships it to the buyer, and sends you the profit. That’s it! They even take care of customer support, returns, and refunds so you don’t have to.
👉🏻Teespring Pros And Cons
You can earn much by promoting your designs on social media. All process (order, shipment, payments) will be done by Teespring upon any purchase. You have to just make a design for product and nothing else.
• Even if you create the best t-shirt design ever, you have to market it completely on your own. Meaning you have to promote it on pintrest, quora, create Facebook ads to drive traffic to Teespring’s website for people to buy your t-shirt.
You’re basically selling Teespring’s t-shirts for them.
• Once you create the design you have nearly 6 days to sell your design or it’s taken down. That’s not a lot of time.

How to Earn Money Online using these two methods.
1. Freelance 
Freelancing is working for yourself, as opposed to working for someone else.
• Learn a skill you have interest in. It could be anytime like writing, web designing, social media handling, graphic designing, email marketing, teaching, logo designing, data entry, video editing etc. 
• Create a Portfolio by working for free for people who need to get their work done.
• Register Yourself on Platforms like Fiverr.com , upwork.com freelancer.in etc. and showcase your portfolio. In starting you will have to charge the minimum amount to get work.
• Start to Earn money eventually
2. Dropshipping
Dropshipping is a great business model for aspiring entrepreneurs to start with because it’s accessible. With dropshipping, you can quickly test different business ideas with limited downside, which lets you learn a lot about how to choose and market in-demand products.
• Start by searching products on wholesale websites like wholesaledock.com or deodap.com etc.
• Initially don’t create a website just start by sharing the products on your instapage, Facebook page or WhatsApp groups. After you start getting regular orders, build a Proper website.

Steps to Turn On Developers Options :-
The procedure can be different for every smartphone. Just do a quick google search for your device.
1. Go to Settings > About Phone
2. Tap Software Info > Tap Build Number seven times.
3. Once developer options are activated, you will see a message that reads, You are now a developer.
4. Go back to the Settings pane, where you will now find Developer options as an entry.

It can also work with standard USB PD devices as well as Apple gadgets (iPhone 7 and newer).
